### 1) Incoming SMS - simulate payment SMS from provider
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/incoming-sms
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: test-key-123

{
  "payer_phone": "+963900000001",
  "receiver_phone": "+963900000002",
  "raw_message": "You received 150.00 SYP from +963900000001, txn TXN-123456",
  "amount": 150,
  "currency": "SYP",
  "txn_id": "TXN-123456"
}

###

### 2) Request Wallet - create / link a wallet
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/wallets/request
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: test-key-123

{
  "amount": 150,
  "wallet_label": "Test Wallet 1",
  "wallet_identifier": "WALLET-001",
  "daily_limit": 1000,
  "metadata": {
    "note": "dev test from REST client"
  }
}

###

### 3) Check payment - verify if payment is valid/available
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/payments/check
Content-Type: application/json
X-API-Key: test-key-123

{
  "amount": 150,
  "currency": "SYP",
  "payer_phone": "+963900000001"
}

###

### 4) Confirm payment - confirm previously checked payment
